Class BacktrackHomomorphism

  • java.lang.Object
    • fr.lirmm.graphik.util.profiler.AbstractProfilable
      • fr.lirmm.graphik.graal.homomorphism.AbstractHomomorphism<T1,T2>
        • fr.lirmm.graphik.graal.homomorphism.AbstractHomomorphismWithCompilation<ConjunctiveQuery,AtomSet>
          • fr.lirmm.graphik.graal.homomorphism.BacktrackHomomorphism
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    ExistentialHomomorphism<ConjunctiveQuery,AtomSet>, ExistentialHomomorphismWithCompilation<ConjunctiveQuery,AtomSet>, Homomorphism<ConjunctiveQuery,AtomSet>, HomomorphismWithCompilation<ConjunctiveQuery,AtomSet>, Profilable

    public class BacktrackHomomorphism
extends AbstractHomomorphismWithCompilation<ConjunctiveQuery,AtomSet>
implements HomomorphismWithCompilation<ConjunctiveQuery,AtomSet>, Profilable
    This Backtrack is inspired by the Baget Jean-François Thesis (Chapter 5) see also "Backtracking Through Biconnected Components of a Constraint Graph" (Jean-François Baget, Yannic S. Tognetti IJCAI 2001)
    Author:
    Clément Sipieter (INRIA) <clement@6pi.fr>
